    <p class="wptripadvisor_t1_P_3 wprev_preview_tcolor1_T1">
        <span class="wptripadvisor_star_imgs_T1"><img decoding="async" src="https://marsawaves.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-tripadvisor-review-slider/public/partials/imgs/tripadvisor_stars_2.png" alt="star rating" class="wptripadvisor_t1_star_img_file">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>I sadly wouldn’t recommend this trip to anyone staying north of Marsa Alam near port ghalib. We felt quite deceived by the information given to us prior to the trip<a class="wprs_rd_more">… read more</a><span class="wprs_rd_more_text" style="display:none;"> which was 4pm tour finish and 5pm hotel drop off, leading us to think it would be a 1 hour drive to the boat. It was actually a 3 hour drive which when you include the 2 and a half hour boat ride meant 11 hours of travel for 2 hours of snorkelling, which was just too much for us especially as my partner gets car sick.<br>
<br>
We didn’t arrive arrive back at our resort until after 9pm and almost missed dinner. <br>
<br>
Another issue was that it turns out the $7 “airport pickup” fee is a mandatory charge for everyone regardless of if you are getting picked up from the airport or not. This confusion meant we didn’t take enough cash on the trip which created an awkward situation with the guide and I had to run to the ATM when we arrived back. <br>
<br>
We did have a few awesome albeit brief encounters with dolphins but don’t expect they to stick around very long with all the boats and tourists chasing them. The RIBs were overfilled with people making entry very chaotic, easy to get kicked by someone when jumping in.</span>				</p>
